Reverted edits by [[Special:Contribs/95.147.134.76|95.147.134.76]] ([[User talk:95.147.134.76|talk]]) to last version by 27.147.204.39
fixed minor mistakes, verified a source

The error was the use of "H" so the letter "ه" to transliterate "خ", as well as the use of "ı" which exists in no transliteration scheme in the infobox. There is no difference in meaning between the informal ending, making the last letter an "a" and the nominative ending in which "ةُ‎" becomes "atu", both are correct. I simply used the spelling with taškīl and grammatical cases from the Arabic Wikipedia. DIN 31635 was last updated in 2011 shouldn't the norm be preferable over a book from the 80s
